item.description:
Iram was a city having columns. Ad b. Us b. Iram had two sons Shadid and Shaddid, who ruled after him. Shadid perished. Shaddad became the sole ruler of the realm, and the kings there submitted to his authority.
When Shaddad heard a description of Paradise, he said= &ldquo;I shall build something like it.&rdquo;
He lived 900 years and built the large city of Iram in the desert of Aden over a period of 300 years.
